
Overview of verb glaze

The verb glaze has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (6) glaze -- (coat with a glaze; "the potter glazed the dishes"; "glaze the bread with eggwhite")
2. (1) glaze, glass, glass over, glaze over -- (become glassy or take on a glass-like appearance; "Her eyes glaze over when she is bored")
3. glass, glaze -- (furnish with glass; "glass the windows")
4. sugarcoat, glaze, candy -- (coat with something sweet, such as a hard sugar glaze)

Overview of adj glazed

The adj glazed has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) glassy, glazed -- ((used of eyes) lacking liveliness; "empty eyes"; "a glassy stare"; "his eyes were glazed over with boredom")
2. glazed, glassed -- (fitted or covered with glass; "four glazed walls")
3. glazed, shiny -- (having a shiny surface or coating; "glazed fabrics"; "glazed doughnuts")
4. glazed -- ((of foods) covered with a shiny coating by applying e.g. beaten egg or a sugar or gelatin mixture; "glazed doughnuts"; "a glazed ham")
